    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/2211.08407v4</id>
    <title>Trust-Awareness to Secure Swarm Intelligence from Data Injection Attack</title>
    <updated>2023-05-10T10:28:53Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2211.08407v4" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2211.08407v4" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>Enabled by the emerging industrial agent (IA) technology, swarm intelligence (SI) is envisaged to play an important role in future industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) that is shaped by Sixth Generation (6G) mobile communications and digital twin (DT). However, its fragility against data injection attack may halt it from practical deployment. In this paper we propose an efficient trust approach to address this security concern for SI.</summary>
